[[en:Ta-asobi]] [[sn:Ta-asobi]] [[ja:田遊び]] [[sn:a-asobi]]
<!--Ta-asobi--> [[Category:予祝芸能]]

'''Ta-asobi''' ({{ill|Ta-asobi|ja|田遊び|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ta-asobi|qq=}}) is a form of {{ill|ritual performance|ja|儀礼的な演技|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/ritual performance|qq=}} in Japan that mimics {{ill|rice cultivation|ja|稲作|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/rice cultivation|qq=}} practices as part of its {{ill|folk performing arts|ja|民俗芸能|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/folk performing arts|qq=}} traditions.
== Overview ==
Ta-asobi is a [[:en:Ritual|ritual]] performance where participants simulate the various stages of rice cultivation to pray for a [[:en:Bumper crop|bountiful harvest]]. It is often held during the [[:en:Japanese New Year|Japanese New Year]] period and is known by different names in various regions, such as {{ill|Otaue Matsuri|ja|御田|1=Sacred rice field|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Otaue Matsuri|13=User:Immanuelle/Sacred rice field|qq=}}, spring plowing ({{ill|Shunkuwa|ja|春鍬|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shunkuwa|qq=}}), spring rice pounding ({{ill|Haruta Uchi|ja|春田打ち|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Haruta Uchi|qq=}}), or rice festival ({{ill|Tamasuri|ja|田祭り|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tamasuri|qq=}}).<ref name=Tsurumi>[https://www.city.yokohama.lg.jp/tsurumi/shokai/gaiyo/rekishi/5_tsurumi/no05-2.html History of Tsurumi No.5: Traditional Arts of Tsurumi, Part 2: Tsurumi’s Rice Festival] (Tsurumi Ward Office)</ref> While details differ regionally, the core ritual often dramatizes the process of sowing seeds to harvesting rice. According to {{ill|Tsunehisa Arai|ja|新井恒易|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsunehisa Arai|qq=}}, over 300 such traditions exist across Japan.
In many Ta-asobi rituals, scenes involving [[:en:Cattle|oxen]] (or [[:en:Horse|horses]]) used for cultivation are key highlights.<ref>{{Cite journal|author=Hoshino Hiroshi|year=1990|title=From Musical Rituals to Bodily Performances|journal=Gestures and Music|publisher=Tokyo Shoseki|pages=199–208}}</ref> Participants often wear a canopy (horokasa) to impersonate oxen, pulling {{ill|plows|ja|犂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/plows|qq=}} and mimicking {{ill|land preparation|ja|田起こし|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/land preparation|qq=}} and {{ill|puddling|ja|代かき|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/puddling|qq=}}. In some performances, oxen are represented by dolls or other substitutes. Variations include unruly oxen scenes or rituals praising and honoring the oxen. [[:en:Shinobu Orikuchi|Nobuo Orikuchi]], in his essay "The Concept of Ta-asobi Rituals," speculated that the oxen might have originally symbolized sacrifices to the [[:en:Ta-no-Kami|rice field deities]], offered to ensure abundant harvests.
== Examples ==
For example, at {{ill|Kitano Tenjin Shrine|ja|北野天神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kitano Tenjin Shrine|qq=}} in {{ill|Tokumaru, Itabashi|ja|徳丸|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokumaru, Itabashi|qq=}}, [[:en:Tokyo|Tokyo]], the annual "Tokumaru Ta-asobi" held on [[:en:February 21|February 21]] is described in the {{ill|Shinpen Musashi Fudoki|ja|新編武蔵風土記稿|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinpen Musashi Fudoki|qq=}} as a sacred ritual referred to as "Ta-asobi Festival." During the event, participants enact rice cultivation processes in a two-ken-square space called a {{ill|mogari|ja|モガリ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/mogari|qq=}} within the shrine precinct. One notable act involves "calling in," during which the farmer characters Taroji and Anjo perform a dance symbolizing union and {{ill|fertility ritual|ja|性的儀礼|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/fertility ritual|qq=}} to evoke abundant harvests.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Shinpen Musashi Fudoki|volume=Volume 14, Toshima District, Section 6|chapter=Tokumaru Motomura / Tokumaru Wakimura, Tenjin Shrine|publisher=Ministry of Home Affairs Geographic Bureau|date=1884-6|id={{NDLJP|763977/56}}}}</ref>
Other related events include {{ill|rice planting dances|ja|田植踊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/rice planting dances|qq=}} and regional performances like {{ill|Hachinohe Enburi|ja|八戸のえんぶり|1=Enburi|2=ja|3=えんぶり|lt=Hachinohe Enburi|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachinohe Enburi|13=User:Immanuelle/Enburi|qq=}} in [[:en:Tōhoku region|Tohoku]].
== Notable Examples of Ta-asobi ==
* The {{ill|Itabashi Ta-asobi|ja|板橋の田遊び|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Itabashi Ta-asobi|qq=}}, a {{ill|Nationally Designated Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property|ja|重要無形民俗文化財|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nationally Designated Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property|qq=}} of [[:en:Itabashi|Itabashi Ward]], [[:en:Tokyo|Tokyo]]. * The "Tsurumi Ta-asobi," a {{ill|Yokohama City Registered Regional Cultural Property|ja|横浜市登録地域文化財|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yokohama City Registered Regional Cultural Property|qq=}} performed at {{ill|Tsurumi Shrine|ja|鶴見神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsurumi Shrine|qq=}} in {{ill|Tsurumi Ward|ja|鶴見区|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsurumi Ward|qq=}}, [[:en:Yokohama|Yokohama]].<ref name=Tsurumi/><ref>[https://www.city.yokohama.lg.jp/kurashi/kyodo-manabi/bunkazai/bunya12000.files/0007_20191120.pdf Yokohama City Cultural Property List (PDF)]</ref> * The "Fujimori Ta-asobi," a Nationally Designated Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property in [[:en:Yaizu|Yaizu City]], [[:en:Shizuoka Prefecture|Shizuoka Prefecture]]. * The "Hirugaya Ta-asobi," performed at {{ill|Hiruko Shrine (Makinohara)|ja|蛭児神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hiruko Shrine (Makinohara)|qq=}} in [[:en:Makinohara|Makinohara City]], [[:en:Shizuoka Prefecture|Shizuoka Prefecture]], also a Nationally Designated Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property. * The "Takizawa Ta-asobi," performed at Takizawa Yasaka Shrine in [[:en:Fujieda, Shizuoka|Fujieda City]], Shizuoka Prefecture, designated as an {{ill|Important Intangible Cultural Property|ja|無形民俗文化財|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Important Intangible Cultural Property|qq=}} of Shizuoka Prefecture. * The "Mishima Ta-asobi," performed at [[:en:Mishima Taisha|Mishima Taisha]] in [[:en:Mishima, Shizuoka|Mishima City]], Shizuoka Prefecture, also an Important Intangible Cultural Property of Shizuoka Prefecture. * The "Oguni Shrine Ta-asobi," performed at {{ill|Okuni Shrine|lt=Okuni Shrine|lt=Oguni Shrine|ja|小國神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oguni Shrine|qq=}} in {{ill|Mori Town, Shuchi District|ja|森町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mori Town, Shuchi District|qq=}}, [[:en:Shizuoka Prefecture|Shizuoka Prefecture]], designated as a {{ill|Intangible Folk Cultural Properties Requiring Documentation|lt=Intangible Folk Cultural Properties Requiring Documentation|lt=Selected Intangible Folk Cultural Property|ja|選択無形民俗文化財|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Selected Intangible Folk Cultural Property|qq=}}.
